{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KoqmvW9QLiYu2JuZn79Egp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ES cluster is up and running HTTPS. The `curl` with exit code 7 means \"couldn't connect to host\". But the logs show it IS receiving connections (plaintext HTTP traffic, and authentication attempts).\n\nWait, exit code 7 from curl means \"Failed to connect to host\". But the logs show the ES node IS responding to HTTPS (and plaintext HTTP).\n\nActually looking more carefully:\n- \"received plaintext http traffic on an https channel\" - this might be the readiness probe or something using HTTP instead of HTTPS\n- \"Authentication of [elastic] was terminated\" - ES is up and running!\nSo the real problem is the readiness probe is failing because it's using the wrong password from the corrupted secret. The ES node itself is healthy and responding, so I need to retry with the correct credentials.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1003,"cache_read_input_tokens":45047,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1003},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55658f27-e9be-4ec1-9fdb-95df7a77ea40","uuid":"cf430e50-6663-4482-bd82-5cd007dd1e59","request_id":"req_011CcLyCp2q5ZkkKyFABxx68"}
