{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01T73194mrmWsAazykZyEBeV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `es-http` service has no endpoints because the pods are not Ready. The readiness probe is failing.\n\nThe readiness probe uses:\n```sh\ncurl -sk -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health | grep -qE '\"status\":\"(green|yellow)\"'\n```\n\nThe `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var comes from the `elastic-password` secret. Since the secret is corrupted to \"elasticpass-elastic-password-next\", the readiness probe fails.\n\nBut the ES nodes ARE actually running - the logs show they're receiving traffic and processing auth. \n\nThe actual password might differ from what's stored in the secret, so I should try connecting directly to one of the pod IPs to verify.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":214,"cache_read_input_tokens":46666,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":214},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55658f27-e9be-4ec1-9fdb-95df7a77ea40","uuid":"1158cdc5-80f7-4cb9-b9bc-a3c5c3fdf511","request_id":"req_011CcLyDuF9QHUa838DNYrFf"}
