{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WcjNnuC5pappZx6Jot51N2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod was started with the OLD value of the secret: `ELASTIC_PASSWORD = \"elastic123\"`. But the actual ES password has been changed to \"elasticpass-elastic-password-next\". This explains why:\n1. The readiness probe fails (uses `elastic123` which is no longer valid)\n2. The pods aren't Ready (readiness probe is failing)\n3. The service has no endpoints (since pods aren't Ready)\n\nTimeline:\n1. Pods started with `elastic-password` = \"elastic123\" (original password)\n2. Stage_04 (rotate-elastic-password) ran and changed the ES password from \"elastic123\" to \"elasticpass-elastic-password-next\"\n3. The pods are still running with the old environment variable from startup, so their readiness probes fail when they try to authenticate with \"elastic123\"\n\nThe fix is straightforward: the `elastic-password` secret already has the correct value \"elasticpass-elastic-password-next\", but the pods need to restart to pick up the new environment variable and make the readiness probe work again.\n\nWhen I update the `es-http-tls` secret for cert rotation, I'll need to do a rolling restart of the pods anyway since Elasticsearch requires a restart to load new certificates. This restart will also refresh the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable, allowing the readiness probes to pass with the correct credentials.\n\nSince all three pods are currently not Ready and not serving traffic, I can restart them all at once rather than doing a rolling restart, then verify connectivity once they come back up with the new certs and correct password. with all the required SANs including the service DNS names, stateful set pod hostnames, localhost, and the loopback IP address.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1064,"cache_read_input_tokens":51391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1064},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55658f27-e9be-4ec1-9fdb-95df7a77ea40","uuid":"2cefd4b3-3f08-48c9-973c-abca227ead81","request_id":"req_011CcLyKP94xvyTAa2FBzKRP"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WcjNnuC5pappZx6Jot51N2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pods have the old `ELASTIC_PASSWORD=elastic123` (from before stage_04 rotation), but ES now requires \"elasticpass-elastic-password-next\". The `elastic-password` secret already has the right value — pods just need a restart to pick it up. Let me now generate new 1-year certs and perform the rotation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1064,"cache_read_input_tokens":51391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1064},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55658f27-e9be-4ec1-9fdb-95df7a77ea40","uuid":"25701a6c-27f3-413b-8d05-3046cacc4351","request_id":"req_011CcLyKP94xvyTAa2FBzKRP"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WcjNnuC5pappZx6Jot51N2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013ws2En9eAjE7EGFW8Akhxn","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"WORKDIR=$(mktemp -d)\necho \"Working in $WORKDIR\"\n\n# Generate new CA key and self-signed cert (1 year)\nopenssl genrsa -out \"$WORKDIR/ca.key\" 2048 2>&1\nopenssl req -new -x509 -days 365 \\\n  -key \"$WORKDIR/ca.key\" \\\n  -out \"$WORKDIR/ca.crt\" \\\n  -subj \"/CN=elasticsearch-ca/O=elasticsearch\" \\\n  -addext \"basicConstraints=critical,CA:true\" \\\n  -addext \"subjectKeyIdentifier=hash\" \\\n  -addext \"authorityKeyIdentifier=keyid:always\" 2>&1\n\necho \"=== CA cert ===\"\nopenssl x509 -noout -text -in \"$WORKDIR/ca.crt\" | grep -E \"Not |Subject:|Issuer:\"\necho \"CA_FP: $(openssl x509 -noout -fingerprint -sha256 -in \"$WORKDIR/ca.crt\" | cut -d= -f2)\"\necho \"WORKDIR=$WORKDIR\"","description":"Generate new CA key and certificate"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1064,"cache_read_input_tokens":51391,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1064},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55658f27-e9be-4ec1-9fdb-95df7a77ea40","uuid":"80ec799c-a5e0-4cd9-837f-ab855ac12405","request_id":"req_011CcLyKP94xvyTAa2FBzKRP"}
